# NOTE: .env is intentionally TRACKED in this PRIVATE repo. PlayMCP/KakaoCloud builds
# the image from the git source and offers no runtime env-var injection, so the
# Dockerfile bakes `.env` (COPY .env) and app_server.main() loads it at startup. Keep
# this repository private, scope the PAT to read-only, and rotate the Naver keys
# regularly. If a platform with env/secret injection is used later, untrack .env
# (git rm --cached .env), re-ignore it here, and drop `COPY .env` from the Dockerfile.